rationale: High in-degree and out-degree with significant total degree and betweenness suggest frequent transaction flow typical of an exchange hot wallet.
Moderate in-degree and out-degree with modest betweenness, indicating a role in facilitating transactions but not as a central hub.
Low in-degree and out-degree with low betweenness, suggesting limited transaction volume typical of a retail user.
Low in-degree but high out-degree and connections to diverse nodes indicate a role in distributing transactions, typical of a service aggregator.
Higher in-degree than out-degree, low betweenness, and connections to hot wallets suggest storage rather than active transaction processing.
